SUMMARY:Palette Pals
DESCRIPTION:It's never a bad time to make new friends! Come make art and 
 meet others with common interests during our monthly friend-finding art g
 roup\, Palette Pals!  Sessions will include art prompts meant to help bui
 ld connection with others\, but if you just want to flex your creative mu
 scles and make what you like\, feel free to bring your own art supplies a
 nd create something while in the company of others!  This group meets on 
 the 3rd Thursday of every month\, excluding holidays and museum closures.
  It is open to everyone: students\, staff\, and the public included! The 
 group will meet in the Roehm Family Art-making Studio\, located inside th
 e Simpson Center for Education on the 2nd floor of the Eskenazi Museum of
  Art.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  It's never a bad time to make new frien
 ds! Come make art and meet others with common interests during our monthl
 y friend-finding art group\, Palette Pals!</p><p>  Sessions will include 
